<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Sciense Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B25" refString="Wu, Y-R, 1965. Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9. Sciense Press, Beijing" title="Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9." year="1965">Wu (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. (1988)</bibRefCitation>
this species was recorded from different provinces of China (Jilin, Hebei, Anhui, Jiangsu, Shandong, Shanghai, Zhejiang, Sichuan, Yunnan, Xizang, Guandong). However, re-identification of specimens from the IZCAS Collection determined by Prof. Wu as 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as the analysis of the descriptive notes given in these works revealed misidentifications. In fact, the specimens from Yunnan (1 ♀, Lijiang) and Sichuan (1 ♂, Barkam; 1 ♀, Xiangcheng) belong to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. pieli" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="pieli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. pieli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two species are very similar structurally and sculpturally, but 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by lack of a longitudinal carina on vertex (also indicated in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" author="Cockerell, TDA" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the United States National Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="1 - 20" refId="B10" refString="Cockerell, TDA, 1922. Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 4. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 60 (2413): 1 - 20, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" title="Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 4." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00963801.60-2413.1" volume="60" year="1922">Cockerell 1922</bibRefCitation>
: 12). In contrast, the longitudinal carina on vertex in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. pieli" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="pieli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. pieli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly developed, corresponding to descriptive notes by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Sciense Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B25" refString="Wu, Y-R, 1965. Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9. Sciense Press, Beijing" title="Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9." year="1965">Wu (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, where pointed on &quot;small process on vertex&quot;. Among determined by Wu specimens we have not found any specimens from Xizang, with records from this province (
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. 1988</bibRefCitation>
) instead referring to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. montanus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, another species similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a vertex carina. So, males of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded by Wu, 1965 and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. 1988</bibRefCitation>
refer to other species, and the male of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. grahami" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="grahami">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. grahami</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unknown. The female of this species is difficult to distinguish from the vicarious West-Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. ephippius" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="species" species="ephippius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">S. ephippius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linné">Linne</normalizedToken>
, 1767) and it is also similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. pellucidus subsp. var. var. gibridus" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" rank="variety" species="pellucidus" subSpecies="var." variety="gibridus">S. pellucidus var. gibridus</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Blüthgen">Bluethgen</normalizedToken>
, 1924. Clarification of the status of this species and possible synonymy is a task for future study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
China (Shanxi, Shaanxi, Shanghai, Sichuan). The records by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ascher, JS" journalOrPublisher="Zoologica Scripta" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" publicationUrl="http://www.discoverlife.org/mp/20q?guide=Apoidea_species" refId="B2" refString="Ascher, JS, Pickering, J, 2020. Discover Life bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila). http://www.discoverlife.org/mp/20q?guide=Apoidea_species" title="Discover Life bee species guide and world checklist (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophila)." url="http://www.discoverlife.org/mp/20q?guide=Apoidea_species" year="2020">Ascher and Pickering 2020</bibRefCitation>
from Jilin, Hebei, Zhejiang, Anhui, Jiangsu, Yunnan, Xizang, Guandong based on misidentification that was published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Sciense Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B25" refString="Wu, Y-R, 1965. Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9. Sciense Press, Beijing" title="Hymenoptera: Apoidea, Chinese Economic Insect Fauna, Vol. 9." year="1965">Wu (1965)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, Y-R" journalOrPublisher="Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" refId="B26" refString="Wu, Y-R, He, W, Wang, SF, 1988. Bee Fauna of Yunnan. Kunming, Yunnan Science and Technology Press" title="Bee Fauna of Yunnan." year="1988">Wu et al. (1988)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
